mate transporters stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource an office of science user facility home mate transporters structure of a cation bound multidrug and toxic compound extrusion transporter posted 2010 mate transporters are responsible for the exportation of various substrates and toxins from cells of bacteria plants and mammals using a proton or sodium gradient plants use them to transport metabolites and they are important for tolerance to aluminum in soil an important factor for crop yield in bacteria and mammals mate transporters are important for multiple drug resistance which affects the efficacy of many medicines although these transporters play such important roles much about how they work is not understood read more fig 1 crystal structure of norm a mate transmembrane transporter 2010 a close look at an important multidrug transporter read more syndicate content the stanford synchrotron radiation lightsource is a directorate of slac national accelerator laboratory which is operated by stanford university for the department of energy other news sources slac today ssrl headlines symmetry magazine lightsources org interactions org ilc newsline spires slac national accelerator laboratory slac national accelerator laboratory menlo park ca operated by stanford university for the us department of energy office of science content owner cathy knotts privacy notice security notice and terms of use doe stanford university
